<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The <code>is</code> attribute creates <strong>customized built-in elements</strong> — native HTML elements enhanced with custom JavaScript behavior. Unlike autonomous custom elements (e.g., <code>&lt;my-component&gt;</code>), customized built-ins inherit all native behavior: semantics, accessibility, form participation, and default styles.</p>
<p>The syntax is <code>&lt;element is="custom-name"&gt;</code>, where the custom element class extends the native element's interface (e.g., <code>HTMLButtonElement</code>, <code>HTMLInputElement</code>).</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>Add the <code>is</code> attribute to a native element to activate the custom behavior registered for that name.</p>

<code-block language="html" label="Customized built-in button">{{ basicExample | escape }}</code-block>

<h2>Registration</h2>
<p>The custom element class must extend the specific element interface, and the <code>define()</code> call must include the <code>extends</code> option.</p>

